    <title>Deploy a Hexo Personal Blog</title>
    <link href="/2025/03/29/Deploy%20a%20Personal%20Blog%20with%20Hexo%20and%20GitHub%20Pages/"/>
    <url>/2025/03/29/Deploy%20a%20Personal%20Blog%20with%20Hexo%20and%20GitHub%20Pages/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This guide walks you through every step to set up, write, preview, and deploy a personal blog using <strong>Hexo</strong> (a fast static site generator), <strong>Node.js</strong>, <strong>Git</strong>, and <strong>GitHub Pages</strong>.</p><hr><h2 id="‚ú®-Overview-of-Tools"><a href="#‚ú®-Overview-of-Tools" class="headerlink" title="‚ú® Overview of Tools"></a>‚ú® Overview of Tools</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Git</strong></td><td>Version control system, helps track and manage changes to your blog code</td></tr><tr><td><strong>GitHub</strong></td><td>Hosts your blog‚Äôs code and publishes it via GitHub Pages</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Node.js</strong></td><td>Required to run Hexo and its plugins</td></tr><tr><td><strong>npm</strong></td><td>Node Package Manager, used to install and manage packages for Node.js</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Hexo</strong></td><td>Static site generator that turns Markdown files into a blog</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Hexo CLI</strong></td><td>Command Line Interface tool for managing Hexo commands</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Markdown Editor</strong></td><td>Tool to conveniently write blog posts in Markdown format</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-1-Install-Prerequisites"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-1-Install-Prerequisites" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 1: Install Prerequisites"></a>‚úÖ Step 1: Install Prerequisites</h2><h3 id="A-Install-Node-js-and-npm"><a href="#A-Install-Node-js-and-npm" class="headerlink" title="A. Install Node.js and npm"></a>A. Install Node.js and npm</h3><ul><li><p>Download from <a href="https://nodejs.org/">https://nodejs.org</a></p></li><li><p>npm comes bundled with Node.js</p></li><li><p><code>npm</code> stands for <strong>Node Package Manager</strong>. It is used to:</p><ul><li><p>üì¶ Install packages (like Hexo, deploy plugins, themes, etc.)</p></li><li><p>üîÑ Manage dependencies in your project</p></li><li><p>üõ†Ô∏è Run scripts (like building or deploying your blog)</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3 id="B-Install-Git"><a href="#B-Install-Git" class="headerlink" title="B. Install Git"></a>B. Install Git</h3><ul><li><p>Download from <a href="https://git-scm.com/">https://git-scm.com</a></p></li><li><p>Git is used to manage version history, push code to GitHub, and collaborate with others</p></li></ul><h3 id="C-Optional-but-recommended-Install-a-Markdown-Editor"><a href="#C-Optional-but-recommended-Install-a-Markdown-Editor" class="headerlink" title="C. (Optional but recommended) Install a Markdown Editor"></a>C. (Optional but recommended) Install a Markdown Editor</h3><ul><li><p><strong>VS Code</strong>: Full-featured, extensible code editor</p></li><li><p><strong>Typora</strong>, <strong>MarkText</strong>, or <strong>Obsidian</strong>: Clean, distraction-free Markdown editors</p></li></ul><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-2-Set-Up-a-Hexo-Blog-Locally"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-2-Set-Up-a-Hexo-Blog-Locally" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 2: Set Up a Hexo Blog Locally"></a>‚úÖ Step 2: Set Up a Hexo Blog Locally</h2><h3 id="A-Install-Hexo-CLI-Command-Line-Interface"><a href="#A-Install-Hexo-CLI-Command-Line-Interface" class="headerlink" title="A. Install Hexo CLI (Command Line Interface)"></a>A. Install Hexo CLI (Command Line Interface)</h3><ul><li><p>Open your terminal (Command Prompt, Git Bash, or VS Code terminal)</p></li><li><p>Run:</p></li></ul><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">npm install -g hexo-cli   <span class="hljs-comment"># -g installs it globally so you can use `hexo` command anywhere</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="B-Create-a-Blog-Project-Folder"><a href="#B-Create-a-Blog-Project-Folder" class="headerlink" title="B. Create a Blog Project Folder"></a>B. Create a Blog Project Folder</h3><ol><li><p>Create or open a folder on your local machine where you want to build your blog (e.g., <code>Documents/BlogProjects</code>)</p></li><li><p>Right-click the folder and select <strong>‚ÄúOpen with Git Bash‚Äù</strong> or open VS Code terminal in that folder</p></li><li><p>Run the following commands:</p></li></ol><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo init my-blog         <span class="hljs-comment"># Initializes a new Hexo project in a folder named &#x27;my-blog&#x27;</span><br><span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> my-blog                <span class="hljs-comment"># Navigates into the new blog folder</span><br>npm install               <span class="hljs-comment"># Installs the required dependencies specified in the package.json</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="C-Test-Your-Blog-Locally"><a href="#C-Test-Your-Blog-Locally" class="headerlink" title="C. Test Your Blog Locally"></a>C. Test Your Blog Locally</h3><ul><li>To preview your blog before publishing:</li></ul><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo server               <span class="hljs-comment"># Starts a local development server</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><ul><li>Then open your browser and go to:</li></ul><figure class="highlight dts"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs dts"><span class="hljs-symbol">http:</span><span class="hljs-comment">//localhost:4000</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-3-Create-and-Connect-a-GitHub-Repository"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-3-Create-and-Connect-a-GitHub-Repository" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 3: Create and Connect a GitHub Repository"></a>‚úÖ Step 3: Create and Connect a GitHub Repository</h2><h3 id="A-Set-up-GitHub"><a href="#A-Set-up-GitHub" class="headerlink" title="A. Set up GitHub"></a>A. Set up GitHub</h3><ul><li><p>Go to <a href="https://github.com/">https://github.com</a> and create a new repository:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Repo name</strong>: <code>yourusername.github.io</code> (must match your GitHub username exactly if it‚Äôs your primary personal site)</p></li><li><p>Leave it <strong>public</strong> and <strong>uninitialized</strong> (no README, .gitignore, etc.)</p></li></ul></li></ul><blockquote><p>üìù Note: You can only have <strong>one</strong> <code>yourusername.github.io</code> repo for your main site, but you can create <strong>additional repos</strong> (e.g., <code>second-blog</code>) for secondary&#x2F;project blogs.</p></blockquote><h3 id="B-Set-up-Git-Locally"><a href="#B-Set-up-Git-Locally" class="headerlink" title="B. Set up Git Locally"></a>B. Set up Git Locally</h3><blockquote><p>Git is necessary to connect your local blog folder with the GitHub repository so you can push your code online.</p></blockquote><p>In Git Bash or terminal:</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">git config --global user.name <span class="hljs-string">&quot;Your Name&quot;</span>          <span class="hljs-comment"># Sets your Git username</span><br>git config --global user.email <span class="hljs-string">&quot;you@example.com&quot;</span>   <span class="hljs-comment"># Sets your Git email</span><br>ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C <span class="hljs-string">&quot;you@example.com&quot;</span>      <span class="hljs-comment"># Generates SSH key to authenticate with GitHub</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Then:</p><ul><li><p>Go to GitHub &gt; Settings &gt; SSH and GPG Keys &gt; New SSH Key</p></li><li><p>Paste the contents of your public key (<code>id_rsa.pub</code>)</p></li></ul><h3 id="C-Connect-Your-Local-Hexo-Folder-to-GitHub"><a href="#C-Connect-Your-Local-Hexo-Folder-to-GitHub" class="headerlink" title="C. Connect Your Local Hexo Folder to GitHub"></a>C. Connect Your Local Hexo Folder to GitHub</h3><p>In your blog project folder:</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash"><span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> my-blog<br>npm install hexo-deployer-git --save      <span class="hljs-comment"># Installs the deployment plugin</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Edit the <code>_config.yml</code> file in your Hexo root directory:</p><figure class="highlight yaml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs yaml"><span class="hljs-attr">deploy:</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class="hljs-string">git</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">repo:</span> <span class="hljs-string">git@github.com:yourusername/yourusername.github.io.git</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">branch:</span> <span class="hljs-string">main</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="D-Deploy-for-the-First-Time"><a href="#D-Deploy-for-the-First-Time" class="headerlink" title="D. Deploy for the First Time"></a>D. Deploy for the First Time</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo clean         <span class="hljs-comment"># Cleans cache and old files</span><br>hexo generate      <span class="hljs-comment"># Converts markdown into HTML static files</span><br>hexo deploy        <span class="hljs-comment"># Pushes your generated files to GitHub</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Then visit:</p><figure class="highlight dts"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs dts"><span class="hljs-symbol">https:</span><span class="hljs-comment">//yourusername.github.io</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-3-5-Hosting-a-Second-Blog-Optional"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-3-5-Hosting-a-Second-Blog-Optional" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 3.5: Hosting a Second Blog (Optional)"></a>‚úÖ Step 3.5: Hosting a Second Blog (Optional)</h2><p>If you want to host multiple blogs on the same GitHub account:</p><ol><li><p><strong>Create a new repository</strong> (e.g., <code>second-blog</code>)</p></li><li><p>In your second Hexo project‚Äôs <code>_config.yml</code>, set:</p></li></ol><figure class="highlight yaml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs yaml"><span class="hljs-attr">deploy:</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">type:</span> <span class="hljs-string">git</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">repo:</span> <span class="hljs-string">git@github.com:yourusername/second-blog.git</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">branch:</span> <span class="hljs-string">gh-pages</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><ol start="3"><li>After deploying, your second blog will be accessible at:</li></ol><figure class="highlight awk"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs awk">https:<span class="hljs-regexp">//y</span>ourusername.github.io<span class="hljs-regexp">/second-blog/</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><blockquote><p>‚úÖ Great for testing, personal sub-blogs, or project documentation.</p></blockquote><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-4-Connect-a-Custom-Domain-Optional"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-4-Connect-a-Custom-Domain-Optional" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 4: Connect a Custom Domain (Optional)"></a>‚úÖ Step 4: Connect a Custom Domain (Optional)</h2><h3 id="A-Buy-a-Domain"><a href="#A-Buy-a-Domain" class="headerlink" title="A. Buy a Domain"></a>A. Buy a Domain</h3><p>You can register a domain using services like:</p><ul><li><p>Namecheap</p></li><li><p>GoDaddy</p></li><li><p>Google Domains</p></li></ul><h3 id="B-Set-Domain-in-GitHub-Repo-Settings"><a href="#B-Set-Domain-in-GitHub-Repo-Settings" class="headerlink" title="B. Set Domain in GitHub Repo Settings"></a>B. Set Domain in GitHub Repo Settings</h3><ol><li><p>Go to your blog repo (<code>yourusername.github.io</code>)</p></li><li><p>Settings ‚Üí Pages ‚Üí Custom domain ‚Üí Enter <code>yourdomain.com</code></p></li></ol><h3 id="C-Set-DNS-Records"><a href="#C-Set-DNS-Records" class="headerlink" title="C. Set DNS Records"></a>C. Set DNS Records</h3><p>In your domain registrar‚Äôs DNS panel, add the following:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Type</strong>: A Record</p></li><li><p><strong>Name</strong>: <code>@</code></p></li><li><p><strong>Value</strong>: GitHub IP addresses:</p><ul><li><p><code>185.199.108.153</code></p></li><li><p><code>185.199.109.153</code></p></li><li><p><code>185.199.110.153</code></p></li><li><p><code>185.199.111.153</code></p></li></ul></li></ul><p>Also add a <strong>CNAME</strong> record:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Name</strong>: <code>www</code></p></li><li><p><strong>Value</strong>: <code>yourusername.github.io</code></p></li></ul><h3 id="D-Add-CNAME-to-Your-Hexo-Blog"><a href="#D-Add-CNAME-to-Your-Hexo-Blog" class="headerlink" title="D. Add CNAME to Your Hexo Blog"></a>D. Add CNAME to Your Hexo Blog</h3><p>Create a file named <code>CNAME</code> (no extension) in the <code>source/</code> folder of your Hexo project:</p><figure class="highlight vim"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs vim">yourdomain.<span class="hljs-keyword">com</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Then:</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo clean &amp;&amp; hexo generate &amp;&amp; hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Now your blog will be available at <code>https://yourdomain.com</code></p><blockquote><p>üõ° Tip: Enable HTTPS in GitHub Pages settings.</p></blockquote><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-5-Adding-Editing-and-Deleting-Posts"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-5-Adding-Editing-and-Deleting-Posts" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 5: Adding, Editing, and Deleting Posts"></a>‚úÖ Step 5: Adding, Editing, and Deleting Posts</h2><blockquote><p>Run these commands inside your Hexo blog folder using a terminal (e.g., Git Bash or VS Code Terminal).</p></blockquote><h3 id="A-Add-a-New-Post"><a href="#A-Add-a-New-Post" class="headerlink" title="A. Add a New Post"></a>A. Add a New Post</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo new <span class="hljs-string">&quot;My First Post&quot;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="B-Edit-a-Post"><a href="#B-Edit-a-Post" class="headerlink" title="B. Edit a Post"></a>B. Edit a Post</h3><p>Use a Markdown editor (e.g., VS Code, Typora) to open <code>source/_posts/your-post.md</code></p><h3 id="C-Delete-a-Post"><a href="#C-Delete-a-Post" class="headerlink" title="C. Delete a Post"></a>C. Delete a Post</h3><p>Delete the corresponding <code>.md</code> file from <code>source/_posts/</code></p><h3 id="D-Preview-Changes-Locally"><a href="#D-Preview-Changes-Locally" class="headerlink" title="D. Preview Changes Locally"></a>D. Preview Changes Locally</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo clean &amp;&amp; hexo generate &amp;&amp; hexo server<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Then open: <code>http://localhost:4000</code></p><h3 id="E-Deploy-Changes"><a href="#E-Deploy-Changes" class="headerlink" title="E. Deploy Changes"></a>E. Deploy Changes</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-6-Change-Blog-Theme"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-6-Change-Blog-Theme" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 6: Change Blog Theme"></a>‚úÖ Step 6: Change Blog Theme</h2><blockquote><p>Run the following commands from the root of your Hexo project.</p></blockquote><h3 id="A-Install-a-Theme-Example-NexT"><a href="#A-Install-a-Theme-Example-NexT" class="headerlink" title="A. Install a Theme (Example: NexT)"></a>A. Install a Theme (Example: NexT)</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash"><span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> themes<br>git <span class="hljs-built_in">clone</span> https://github.com/theme-next/hexo-theme-next next<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="B-Set-Theme-in-config-yml"><a href="#B-Set-Theme-in-config-yml" class="headerlink" title="B. Set Theme in _config.yml"></a>B. Set Theme in <code>_config.yml</code></h3><figure class="highlight yaml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs yaml"><span class="hljs-attr">theme:</span> <span class="hljs-string">next</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="C-Rebuild-and-Deploy"><a href="#C-Rebuild-and-Deploy" class="headerlink" title="C. Rebuild and Deploy"></a>C. Rebuild and Deploy</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo clean &amp;&amp; hexo generate &amp;&amp; hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Step-7-Add-Comment-System-Valine-Waline"><a href="#‚úÖ-Step-7-Add-Comment-System-Valine-Waline" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Step 7: Add Comment System (Valine &#x2F; Waline)"></a>‚úÖ Step 7: Add Comment System (Valine &#x2F; Waline)</h2><blockquote><p>Use a code editor (e.g., VS Code) to modify configuration files. Run commands from the root of your blog folder.</p></blockquote><h3 id="A-Choose-a-Comment-System"><a href="#A-Choose-a-Comment-System" class="headerlink" title="A. Choose a Comment System"></a>A. Choose a Comment System</h3><ul><li><p><a href="https://valine.js.org/">Valine</a> ‚Äì requires LeanCloud</p></li><li><p><a href="https://waline.js.org/">Waline</a> ‚Äì Vercel&#x2F;self-hosted</p></li></ul><h3 id="B-Edit-Theme-Config"><a href="#B-Edit-Theme-Config" class="headerlink" title="B. Edit Theme Config"></a>B. Edit Theme Config</h3><p>Edit <code>themes/next/_config.yml</code>:</p><figure class="highlight yaml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs yaml"><span class="hljs-attr">valine:</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">enable:</span> <span class="hljs-literal">true</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">appId:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&lt;your-app-id&gt;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">appKey:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&lt;your-app-key&gt;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="C-Rebuild-and-Deploy-1"><a href="#C-Rebuild-and-Deploy-1" class="headerlink" title="C. Rebuild and Deploy"></a>C. Rebuild and Deploy</h3><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">hexo clean &amp;&amp; hexo generate &amp;&amp; hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h2 id="‚úÖ-Done"><a href="#‚úÖ-Done" class="headerlink" title="‚úÖ Done!"></a>‚úÖ Done!</h2><p>You now have a complete Hexo blog that supports writing, theming, commenting, custom domains, automation, and mobile writing.</p><p>Let me know if you‚Äôd like to export this as a Markdown or PDF file!</p><h2 id="üì§-Blog-Deployment-Overview"><a href="#üì§-Blog-Deployment-Overview" class="headerlink" title="üì§ Blog Deployment Overview"></a>üì§ Blog Deployment Overview</h2><p>A quick recap of how Hexo + GitHub Pages works:</p><ol><li><p>Write Markdown posts</p></li><li><p>Hexo generates static HTML files</p></li><li><p><code>hexo server</code> previews the site locally</p></li><li><p><code>hexo deploy</code> pushes it to GitHub</p></li><li><p>GitHub Pages hosts your blog at <code>https://yourusername.github.io</code></p></li></ol><hr><h2 id="üö®-Common-Errors-Solutions"><a href="#üö®-Common-Errors-Solutions" class="headerlink" title="üö® Common Errors &amp; Solutions"></a>üö® Common Errors &amp; Solutions</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Error</th><th>Solution</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>hexo: command not found</code></td><td>Install Hexo globally: <code>npm install -g hexo-cli</code></td></tr><tr><td><code>Permission denied (publickey)</code></td><td>Check SSH key, ensure it‚Äôs added to GitHub</td></tr><tr><td><code>Cannot find module</code></td><td>Run <code>npm install</code> to install dependencies</td></tr><tr><td>Blog doesn‚Äôt update</td><td>Run <code>hexo clean</code> before generating</td></tr><tr><td>GitHub Pages 404</td><td>Check repo name and branch, and wait a few minutes</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h2 id="üöÄAdvanced-Feature-WIP"><a href="#üöÄAdvanced-Feature-WIP" class="headerlink" title="üöÄAdvanced Feature (WIP)"></a>üöÄAdvanced Feature (WIP)</h2><h3 id="Auto-Deployment-with-GitHub-Actions"><a href="#Auto-Deployment-with-GitHub-Actions" class="headerlink" title="Auto Deployment with GitHub Actions"></a>Auto Deployment with GitHub Actions</h3><p>Sample GitHub Actions Workflow</p><p>Create <code>.github/workflows/deploy.yml</code>:</p><figure class="highlight yaml"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs yaml"><span class="hljs-attr">name:</span> <span class="hljs-string">Deploy</span> <span class="hljs-string">Hexo</span> <span class="hljs-string">Blog</span><br><span class="hljs-attr">on:</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">push:</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">branches:</span><br>      <span class="hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class="hljs-string">main</span><br><span class="hljs-attr">jobs:</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">build:</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">runs-on:</span> <span class="hljs-string">ubuntu-latest</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">steps:</span><br>      <span class="hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class="hljs-attr">uses:</span> <span class="hljs-string">actions/checkout@v3</span><br>      <span class="hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class="hljs-attr">uses:</span> <span class="hljs-string">actions/setup-node@v3</span><br>        <span class="hljs-attr">with:</span><br>          <span class="hljs-attr">node-version:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&#x27;18&#x27;</span><br>      <span class="hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class="hljs-attr">run:</span> <span class="hljs-string">npm</span> <span class="hljs-string">install</span><br>      <span class="hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class="hljs-attr">run:</span> <span class="hljs-string">npx</span> <span class="hljs-string">hexo</span> <span class="hljs-string">generate</span><br>      <span class="hljs-bullet">-</span> <span class="hljs-attr">uses:</span> <span class="hljs-string">peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v3</span><br>        <span class="hljs-attr">with:</span><br>          <span class="hljs-attr">github_token:</span> <span class="hljs-string">$&#123;&#123;</span> <span class="hljs-string">secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN</span> <span class="hljs-string">&#125;&#125;</span><br>          <span class="hljs-attr">publish_dir:</span> <span class="hljs-string">./public</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h3 id="Local-Mobile-Writing-Workflow"><a href="#Local-Mobile-Writing-Workflow" class="headerlink" title="Local + Mobile Writing Workflow"></a>Local + Mobile Writing Workflow</h3><h5 id="A-On-Your-Computer"><a href="#A-On-Your-Computer" class="headerlink" title="A. On Your Computer"></a>A. On Your Computer</h5><p>From your Hexo blog folder:</p><ul><li><p>Use VS Code or Typora to write Markdown files in <code>source/_posts/</code></p></li><li><p>Use Git to version and push changes:</p></li></ul><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash">git add .<br>git commit -m <span class="hljs-string">&quot;Add post&quot;</span><br>git push origin main<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h5 id="B-On-Mobile"><a href="#B-On-Mobile" class="headerlink" title="B. On Mobile"></a>B. On Mobile</h5><ul><li><p>You can:</p><ul><li><p>Use GitHub App to edit and commit</p></li><li><p>Use Termux (Android) + SSH to write with nano&#x2F;vim</p></li><li><p>Use <a href="https://github.com/coder/code-server">code-server</a> for browser-based VS Code</p></li></ul></li></ul><hr><h4 id="One-click-Init-Deploy-Script-Bash"><a href="#One-click-Init-Deploy-Script-Bash" class="headerlink" title="One-click Init + Deploy Script (Bash)"></a>One-click Init + Deploy Script (Bash)</h4><p>Save this as <code>hexo-init.sh</code> and run it in Git Bash:</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs bash"><span class="hljs-meta">#!/bin/bash</span><br><span class="hljs-built_in">read</span> -p <span class="hljs-string">&quot;Enter blog folder name: &quot;</span> folder<br>hexo init <span class="hljs-string">&quot;<span class="hljs-variable">$folder</span>&quot;</span><br><span class="hljs-built_in">cd</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;<span class="hljs-variable">$folder</span>&quot;</span><br>npm install<br>npm install hexo-deployer-git --save<br><span class="hljs-built_in">cat</span> &lt;&lt;<span class="hljs-string">EOF &gt;&gt; _config.yml</span><br><span class="hljs-string"></span><br><span class="hljs-string">deploy:</span><br><span class="hljs-string">  type: git</span><br><span class="hljs-string">  repo: git@github.com:yourusername/yourusername.github.io.git</span><br><span class="hljs-string">  branch: main</span><br><span class="hljs-string">EOF</span><br>hexo clean &amp;&amp; hexo generate &amp;&amp; hexo deploy<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><blockquote><p>üí° Replace <code>yourusername</code> with your GitHub username.</p></blockquote><hr>]]></content>
    
    
    
